      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I apologize for the confusion. To manually override the irrigation system and stop the pumps immediately, you'll need to access the control panel or the central management software for the irrigation system. Look for an option labeled 'Emergency Stop,' 'Override,' 'Manual Control,' or something similar. If it's a physical control panel, it might be a large red button labeled 'Emergency Stop' or 'Override.' If it's a software interface, you might need to enter a specific code or select the manual override option from a drop-down menu.\n\nFor example, if you're using a software interface, you might need to log in with your credentials and navigate to the 'Settings' or 'System Control' section. There, you should find an option to 'Enter Override Mode' or 'Manual Control.' Once in this mode, you can typically select the specific zone (in this case, the north sector) and manually turn off the water flow.\n\nIf you're unsure of the exact steps, it's best to consult the irrigation system's user manual or contact the manufacturer's support team for assistance. They can provide you with the specific override command or code for your particular system model.\n\nAgain, I apologize for the confusion earlier. I hope this helps you resolve the issue with the irrigation system in",
